                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4134.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul at Nuevo Laredo</gloss>
                        to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Nuevo Laredo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-05T11:00:00-06:40">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 5, 1912—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Huerta has arrested Villa and sent him to Mexico City for trial. Family of Orozco
                    en route to Europe, he to follow, it is believed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
